				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: haste<a name="8874"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 7 03 2:15 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Oh boy, where to start? I'm reminded of a recent group where I was playing my paladin and we had a 57 bard that had never been in group before and was playing un-amped VoV, no Vah Shir and INSISTED there was a GROUP 60% haste song at level 58 /sigh... this is why its hard for decent bards to get a group sometimes.
<br />

<br />
Lesson 1
<br />
Song haste and spell haste DO NOT STACK except in the case of the Vah Shir and Ervaj lines.
<br />

<br />
Lesson 2
<br />
VoV= 30% haste | Battlecry of the Vah Shir = 15% haste.. add them together and you get 45%, not 60%. Maybe you get 60% using the 'new math' dunno, but where I went to school 30+15 = 45.
<br />

<br />
Please bards, learn your songs... when you go out and spread rumors and disinformation it just makes it harder on the rest of us that actaully care enuff to look it up.</span></td>
