				<td colspan="2"><span>*begin rant*
<br />

<br />
I can't open your link here at work, due to filters the government puts in place, but there is no website you can show me that will convince me bard haste does not stack with chanter/shamie haste.  Have you ever just WATCHED your character, or the damage output of yourself or your group without and then with your haste song on top of the chanter/shamie haste?  Unless your computer sucks so bad it can not refresh the screeen fast enough you will see the difference, and if you have a parser you can read the difference in DPS.  The only way your bard haste will not stack is if the player is already at their cap with just the shamie/chanter haste.  At lower levels this is completely possible, since your haste cap is quite low.  However as you level up and your haste cap increases beyond what your hast item and chanter/shamie buff can reach, you will easily see the difference our songs make.  Add to that our songs that raise the cap of course for max effect.
<br />

<br />
Remember, do a test yourself, or if all else fails, use your own eyes, before you believe something someone else posts on the internet.  People post a lot of bunk sometimes, just because they can, or sometimes because they believe it to be accurate.  However that does not make it true.  (heck, I have been guilty of the second error a number of times myself in various forums.  I was however corrected, and glad of it.)  And remember, &quot;there are lies, d*mn lies, and statistics&quot;  You can take statistics on anything and twist them around to provide &quot;proof&quot; of just about anything,  but it still doesn't change the truth.
<br />

<br />
*end rant*
