				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: haste<a name="9669"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 31 03 6:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I never said I was not interested in fact, I said there is no website that can convince me it is not happening... there is a big difference.  I could just as well have been saying there is no website you can show me that will convince me the world is flat.  Have you ever measured this yourself?
<br />

<br />
To conduct a scientific study of haste stacking first make sure that neither the spell haste nor the bard haste will put the character being measured at cap, if either one caps the player then obviously they will not stack, since nothing except a couple of our special songs will exceep the cap.
<br />

<br />
Next make sure the battle spam messages are set so that they will show all attacks, whether they are hits or misses.
<br />

<br />
Then find target mobs that are equal in level every time they spawn, and get a shamie or chanter to haste your target character.  Attack many of these mobs, recording how many attacks are made per minute.  Then do the same test with just bard haste on, attacking many of the same creatures and record how many attacks are made per minute.  Then get the shamie or enchanter to cast the same haste spell on you again and sing the same haste song again and attack the same mobs again, recording your number of attacks per minute.  Don't record DPS, record number of attacks, because some haste spells and songs add to attack rating which will increase average damage.
<br />

<br />
Do this test yourself, do not rely on what someone else posted, before you go calling people stupid.  And like I said WATCH your screen.  There is a reason I will not believe someone else's test over what I have observed myself.  I have taken many classes in statistics and also many lab sciences so I know how to conduct an experiment in a controlled maner, and I also know how to report statistics.  And I know that statistics can be manipulated to &quot;show&quot; what ever you want them to, especially when your target audience is willing to believe what you are &quot;prooving&quot; to them.  You are a very oppinionated person, and should base your oppinions on your own observations/tests rather than someone elses statistics so that you can be more sure of what you are saying, or at least more accurate in what you are sure about.
<br />
Believing that there is a banana in the trashcan will not make one appear there, you may believe it with all your heart and be sure that if you walked over and looked it would be there, but if it isn't, it simply isn't.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
and as far as being laughed at and considered stupid... you are the first to call me so.  More common are my fellow players complaining how slow they feel after I leave and they 'only' have chanter haste or shamie haste.
<br />

<br />
