				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: haste<a name="12620"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 27 03 8:04 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'd recommand twisting Amplification in. With Amp your DS should be around 33pts (great for soloing hordes of greens in lower level dungeons that would otherwise zerg you down btw)! With a mage of about the same level, the dmg shield is 66pts, which is quite noticable. Now I would add another singing-line song to your twist to get the maximum benefit from your Amp. I like Largo's Absonant Binding when I'm on snare duty as it has a huge Agi and a decent AC debuff. Once you reach 58, you can twist in Niv's Harmonic instead for further AC and thus dmg mitigation, if you like.
<br />
So my lineup would be: 
<br />
1. Amplification
<br />
2. Niv's Harmonic/Largo's Absonant Binding
<br />
3. Psalm of Warmth/Cooling/Purity/Vitality
<br />
4. McVaxius' Rousing Rondo
<br />
This is, if you have enough haste due to a chanter or a Shammy, and your stats are doing pretty well with other buffs already. This lineup has atleast one flaw though: If you have haste from a Chanter or Shammy, the mobs you are fighting are probably slowed, making the dmg shield somewhat less efficient. If you dont have slowed mobs, i.e you dont have a haster, hasting the entire group with a better haste than Mc's as well as buffing their stats might be more efficient. 
<br />
Just a thought though  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />
</span></td>
