				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: haste<a name="72758"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 31 05 11:00 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Im pretty sure that bard haste DOES stack with shammie/chanter haste.  The problem is, chanters get a 64% haste, and most toons have a wearable haste (also stackable) of around 22-36%.  The haste cap (once you hit the right level) stays at 100% I think (I have heard it is 94% as well) What does this mean?  It means that your 45% haste gives anywhere from 0-14% haste.  So, the point of this song is to add STR, ATK, and, most importantly (IMHO) DS. To the little haste that you actually need to provide...that is, besides overhaste.  This is how I have found it to work, if Bard haste and chanter haste didnt stack, why would your song still appear in the window?  Also, I totally agree with seeing a difference between not bard hasted and hasted at lower levels, this is prolly 'cause chanter haste back then was like 40% or something (not taking the time to look it up).  Okay, just my 2cp worth. </span></td>
